{
  "texts": [
    "XAI approaches are starting to shed light on the reasoning mechanisms of LLMs (Zhao et al., 2024a), but further research is needed for them to produce reliable proxies of the trustworthiness of LLM outputs.",
    "Finally, effective interaction between humans and LLMs requires a form of mutual understanding that involves a theory of mind (ToM; Premack and Woodruff, 1978) -the ability to infer what others are thinking and how this differs from our own thoughts, a crucial precondition for effective communication and cooperation.",
    "Recent studies (van Duijn et al., 2023; Kosinski, 2024; Strachan et al., 2024) have shown that larger LLMs, such as GPT-4, made significant progress in ToM, performing on par with, and sometimes even surpassing, humans under certain conditions.",
    "However, this competence primarily reflects an ability to simulate human-like responses rather than a genuine mastery of the cognitive processes involved in ToM reasoning.",
    "Achieving authentic ToM in LLMs will require further advancements, such as leveraging external memory systems (Li and Qiu, 2023; Schuurmans, 2023) and, eventually, developing machine metacognition (Johnson et al., 2024)."
  ]
}